  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate the clinical outcome and safety of flutter mucus
      clearance devices.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Respiratory diseases are still increasing in elder population. Sputum detaining is a common
      contributing factor to acute exacerbation. The fluttering mucus clearance technique is
      expected to be a physical assisting therapy enhancing airway secretion clearance but need
      more clinical randomized control trial evidence.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
